-- Barclays Sued by U.S. Regulator Over Mortgage Security Sales
-- B y   J e s s e   H a m i l t o n
-- 2012-09-25T20:29:58Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-09-25/barclays-sued-by-u-s-regulator-over-mortgage-security-sales.html
Barclays Plc is being sued by the
U.S. regulator of credit unions, which says the bank sold $555
million in misrepresented mortgage-backed securities that
contributed to two lender failures.  The National Credit Union Administration announced the suit
filed in federal court in Kansas in a statement today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jesse Hamilton in Washington at 
 jhamilton33@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Maura Reynolds  at   mreynolds34@bloomberg.net . 